
Installing ParaStation
------------------------------

Extract the tar file psm_xxx.tgz

>cd /
>tar xvfz psm_xxx.tgz


Create the parastation device 

>mknod /dev/psm c 40 0
>chmod 666 /dev/psm


Edit the parastation configuration file
/opt/parastation/config/psm.config:


Append parastation services to /etc/services

/etc/services:
# ParaStation entries
psrdp            886/udp       # ParaStation Daemon RDP port
psld             887/tcp       # ParaStation Licensedaemon start port
psid             888/tcp       # ParaStation Daemon start port
psids            889/tcp       # ParaStation Daemon-connection port
psmcast         1889/udp       # ParaStation MCAST port
# end of ParaStation entries 



Append parastation daemons to the (x)inetd configuration


xinetd (RedHat):
-----------------
/etc/xinetd.d/parastation:
#
# ParaStation daemon
#
service psid
{
        disable = no
        socket_type     = stream
        wait            = no
        user            = root
        server          = /opt/parastation/bin/psid
        server_args     =
        log_on_failure  += USERID
}
#
# ParaStation license server
#
service psld
{
        disable = no
        socket_type     = stream
        wait            = no
        user            = root
        server          = /opt/parastation/bin/psld
        server_args     =
        log_on_failure  += USERID
}


inetd (SuSE):
------
/etc/inetd.conf:
#
# ParaStation daemon
#
psid     stream  tcp     nowait  root   /usr/sbin/tcpd /opt/parastation/bin/psid          psid
#
# ParaStation license server
#
psld     stream  tcp     nowait  root   /usr/sbin/tcpd /opt/parastation/bin/psld          psld




Reload the inetd.conf
SuSE: rcinetd reload
RedHat: /etc/rc.d/init.d/xinetd reload




Testing 

start 
/opt/parastation/bin/psiadmin -c "s all"

repeat until all nodes are up.










